summary: I don't think Jon has really bent the knee. When he had the worst of odds against Ramsay, he refused to give in. He knew he was...
body: I don’t think Jon has really bent the knee. When he had the worst of odds against Ramsay, he refused to give in. He knew he was going to lose and yet, he still stuck to his guns. So, why is it that he would give in so easily after he fought so hard for his home? It doesn’t make sense. You dont argue that Northerners are loyal to their own and have chosen you as their king and then proceed to just give up your kingdom because you got rescued from an unnecessary mission.

summary: okay so i have this headcanon
body:
okay so i have this headcanon

ik it’s gonna be a bit controversial so don’t read if you don’t like incest but this is game of thrones??? TW: brief mention of Rape at the beginning

okay here goes:

Rhaegar did in fact kidnap Lyanna and rape her but she wasn’t pregnant by him. she was impregnanted by Brandon Stark, whom she loved not as a brother. Rickard Stark went to the mad king to fight for his daughter but Brandon went to fight for his Beloved. Rickard didn’t know of Brandon and Lyanna’s relations but Ned and Benjen knew. Ned because he happened to catch them once and Benjen because he was closest to Lyanna. (we all know Ned can keep a secret).

It wasn’t Robert who defeated Rhaegar, but Ned, for stealing his sister and for the mad king killing his father and brother. But instead of being king of the seven kingdoms, He and Robert split it and Ned became King of the North, The Trident and Riverlands, The Vale and the Iron Islands. With Robert ruling over everything else. Now Ned and his lips of steel found Lyanna, who told him the true father after he told her that Rhaegar had fell in battle, and vowed to look after her boy. (this we know) Lyanna is the one who named him Jon because Brandon has said that he wanted a son called Jon.

Ned brought him to Winterfell where he met his own son Robb and publicly named him his bastard but never allowed anyone to treat him like one. because in truth he is a bastard as Brandon and Lyanna we’re not wed but he is full blooded Stark and was treated as such. Ned Told Catelyn that he was Lyanna’s boy but never disclosed who his father was.

Catelyn didn’t treat jon bad like in the books and show lore but she did show a dislike for him as she knew who his father was all along because Ned talks in his sleep. she is afraid that Jon will take Robb’s place as next lord of Winterfell. Jon cannot legally have it despite being Brandon’s son, as bastards are last in line for anything, if in line at all.

But Catelyn watched how Ned raised his boys and taught them how to treat their girls i.e. Sansa. It became apparent to Catelyn quite quickly that Ned was grooming Jon to marry Sansa, and although she protested because he was being raised as her brother she relented and began keeping Sansa away from Jon, to prevent the sibling bond they might have grown.

When Robb and Jon are 15 and Sansa 12, they are told of his true parentage and that they have been set to marry since Sansa learned to walk. Robb doesn’t stop thinking of Jon as his brother but he does give him a stern talking to as if they hadn’t been raised together by the same man. because yanno it’s his job as her big brother. Sansa begins to avoid Jon except at the dinners where she sits beside him. not because she had to but because she felt that’s what she was meant to do as his Lady to be.

At his 16 nameday, Ned gifts Jon a keep and names him a Lord. But he cannot live in it until he is married, as Sansa is not old enough to be married yet. It’s a small keep but homey, and needs a lot of work. so over the next few years Jon and Robb are slowly making it livable. and by the time Sansa is 16 is it completely ready.

They are married under the Heart Tree as starks. he cloaks her with a grey cloak with a white wolf as he makes her his wife.

they move into the keep and have 78 children and die when they’re 109
